      "content": "it's looking a bit better now that the pressure is on, so it's not like it's gushing anymore. plus i actually have some manuka honey here in the cupboard. if i just apply a thick layer of this and wrap it tight with a clean cloth, it should seal the wound and stop any bacteria from getting in, right? it seems way safer and easier than driving across town in the dark for stitches.",
